annotationA: Myogenic-determination protein; Nautilus (Nau) belongs to the bHLH family of transcription factors. It is the unique Drosophila ortholog of the mammalian family of bHLH Myogenic Regulatory Factors. Nau is involved in somatic muscle myogenesis
annotationB: Muscle LIM protein at 60A is a Zinc-ion binding protein, expressed strongly in the Z-band region of the sarcomere. It is involved in development and maintenance of the embryonic and flight muscles
